===Etymology===
From a variety of spellings in {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|xno|en}} and {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|surnom||surname}}, formed from Old French {{term|sur-|lang=fro}} ("super-"; earlier ''sor-'', ''sour-'', etc.) + {{term|nom||name|lang=fro}},<ref name=oed>Oxford English Dictionary. "surname, n."</ref> a [[calque]] of late {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|supernomen|supernōmen|lang=la}} and {{term|supranomen|suprānōmen|surname|lang=la}}, from Latin {{term|super-||over, above, beyond|lang=la}} and {{term|nomen|nōmen|name|lang=la}}.<ref name=oed2>Oxford English Dictionary. "surnoun, n."</ref>

